[[File:Kyoto protocol parties and 2012-2020
commitments.svg|thumb|400px|Participation in the Kyoto Protocol



]]

As of June 2013, there are 192 parties to the '[[Kyoto Protocol]]' to the United
Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change. This total includes 191 states
(189 United Nations member states as well as the Cook Islands and Niue) and one
supranational union (the European Union). aimed at
combating global warming. Canada denounced the convention effective 15 December
2012 and ceased to be a member from that date.
categories: Lists of parties to treaties|Kyoto Protocol
